responses.text:
O God! Thou art my God alone;  
In silent dawn, I seek Thy face,  
Beneath the stars, my spirit grown,  
Longs for Thy gentle, holy grace.  

No idol claims my wandering heart,  
No fleeting shadow tempts me now;  
For in Thy light, all fears depart,  
And hope returns upon my brow.  

O Shepherd kind, O King above,  
Thy rod and staff my soul obey;  
I rest within Thy boundless love,  
And trust Thee wholly, come what may.  

O God! Thou art my God alone;  
Thy name upon my lips I raise;  
Forever shall my song be known—  
A hymn of thanks, a life of praise.
